<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36168c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36168c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36168c"> 168(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nonsectarian / disperse!</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The religious instruction in the Board Schools is of course <mark>unsectarian</mark>; the whole school assembles in the morning in the central hall, the children marching in to a band of their own. &hellip; After saluting the headmaster and teachers a hymn is sung, some simple prayers are said, and then the children <mark>disperse</mark> to their class-rooms for half an hour&apos;s religious instruction based on selected parts of the Bible. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 395</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
